	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Written to `research/frameworks/autogen.md`. The file covers:\n\n- **Overview** — MS Research origins, the November 2024 governance split, four active lineages, PyPI naming confusion\n- **Architecture** — `ConversableAgent`/`AssistantAgent`/`UserProxyAgent` hierarchy with code examples, GroupChat with FSM speaker selection, and the v0.4 async actor model rewrite\n- **Communication model** — turn-taking mechanics, group chat broadcast pattern, nested chats, v0.4 typed event publishing\n- **Tool system** — function registration pattern (`register_for_llm` / `register_for_execution`), the self-correcting code execution loop via Docker\n- **Memory** — conversation history as primary context, `TeachableAgent` + ChromaDB for persistent memos\n- **GitHub/Community** — stats table (56.3k stars), AG2 fork situation explained clearly\n- **Strengths/Weaknesses** — balanced, technically specific\n- **Comparison table** — AutoGen vs acteon-swarm across 7 dimensions with prose analysis" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
