	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Written to `research/frameworks/agentscope.md` (~1,100 words). The file covers:\n\n- **Overview**: Alibaba/ModelScope origins, Apache 2.0, Python 3.10+ requirement\n- **Architecture**: `Msg`, `AgentBase`, five pipeline primitives (sequential/parallel/if-else/switch/loop), `MsgHub` broadcast\n- **Distributed model**: actor-based gRPC transport, transparent `.to_dist()` promotion, proxy pattern\n- **Tool system**: `ServiceToolkit`, built-in services (web search, code exec, DB, file I/O), `ReActAgent` loop\n- **Memory**: `TemporaryMemory`, `KnowledgeBank` vector store integration, per-agent isolation caveat\n- **Strengths/Weaknesses**: honest assessment including the gRPC operational overhead and smaller Western mindshare\n- **Comparison with acteon-swarm**: structured table covering scale, transport, fault tolerance, and fit — enterprise distributed platform vs lightweight orchestration" ;
