Persistent cross-session learning via knowledge graph\n- True end-to-end autonomy — no manual stepping required\n- Kali Linux container + 20+ tools out of the box\n- CI/CD embeddable\n- Per-agent model optimization (different LLMs for reasoning vs. execution)\n\n**Weaknesses**\n- No platform-level scope enforcement — relies on user ethics\n- Human trust gap: acts as orchestrator, not co-pilot; hard to audit under real engagement scrutiny\n- Cannot exploit without a pre-existing vulnerability\n- Execution monitoring still in beta; flows can get stuck\n- Docker runtime required — no rootless/restricted env support\n- Despite 13.8k stars, community discussion is thin (~3 active threads)\n- MIT license with AGPL-3.0 cloud SDK carve-out adds licensing complexity\n\n---\n\n### 10. Community Reception\n\n- **13,800 stars, 1,700 forks** — strong initial surge; trended on GitHub Feb 2026\n- Sentiment: predominantly positive on GitHub and tech blogs\n- Security community criticism: dual-use concerns; preference for human-in-the-loop tools in actual engagements\n- Issue tracker: ~15 open — relatively clean for the project's scale\n- Discussion participation: modest; mostly consumers, not co-developers\n\n---\n\n### 11. acteon-swarm References\n\n**None found anywhere.** PentAGI uses its own custom orchestration (FlowProvider / FlowToolsExecutor). No references to acteon-swarm, CrewAI, AutoGen, or any third-party swarm framework appear in the repo, README, DeepWiki docs, or community discussions.\n\n---\n\n### Sources\n\n- [GitHub - vxcontrol/pentagi](https://github.com/vxcontrol/pentagi)\n- [DeepWiki - vxcontrol/pentagi](https://deepwiki.com/vxcontrol/pentagi)\n- [DeepWiki - AI Agents detail](https://deepwiki.com/vxcontrol/pentagi/5-ai-agents)\n- [PentAGI Explained](https://hoangyell.com/pentagi-explained/)\n- [Cybersecurity News](https://cybersecuritynews.com/pentagi-penetration-testing-tool/)\n- [SitePoint - Security Patterns from PentAGI](https://www.sitepoint.com/security-