	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Written to `research/frameworks/crewai.md` — 1,959 words of substantive content (well above the 800–1200 word target; the extra length comes from the code examples and tables).\n\nThe file covers all required sections:\n\n- **Overview** — founding, v1.12.2, MIT, Python 3.10–3.13, 100k+ certified devs\n- **Architecture** — two-layer Flows + Crews model, Agent/Task/Crew with full field tables and code examples, both process models\n- **Communication** — hub-and-spoke constraint explained, delegation mechanics, comparison note vs. AutoGen\n- **Tools** — built-in library, `BaseTool`/`@tool` decorator pattern, MCP integration with code example\n- **Memory** — four-tier table (short/long/entity/user), backend config example, knowledge sources with supported formats\n- **GitHub & Community** — 47,400+ stars, 6,400+ forks, enterprise tier, certified dev count\n- **Strengths/Weaknesses** — 8 each, specific and balanced\n- **Comparison with acteon-swarm** — 10-row table covering metaphor, orchestration, communication, state, tools, parallelism, and a prose recommendation heuristic\n- **References** — 8 links" ;
