# === memory-4b33cf56-f8b4-465f-8759-d3aba91fb2af ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:memory-4b33cf56-f8b4-465f-8759-d3aba91fb2af> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-28T15:14:20.735311Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research CrewAI\",\"Web research CrewAI\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/tool_name> "researcher" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/structured_data> "null" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "a0468aff-ce34-42cc-aca1-e39a62e19fa8" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "episodic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-28T15:14:20.735063+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "The write was blocked — please approve the file write to save the report, or I can present the findings inline. Here's the complete research summary:\n\n---\n\n## CrewAI Research Findings\n\n### Repository Stats\n- **Stars**: 47,400+ | **Forks**: 6,400+ | **License**: MIT\n- **Latest stable**: v1.12.2 (March 26, 2026), pre-release v1.13.0rc1 (March 27, 2026)\n- Python 3.10–3.13, fully independent of LangChain\n- **100,000+** developers certified via learn.crewai.com\n\n---\n\n### Architecture — Two-Layer Model\n```\nFLOWS (structural: state, event-driven logic, branching)\n  └── CREWS (execution: autonomous agent teams on complex tasks)\n```\n- **Flows** orchestrate the overall pipeline with conditional logic and state\n- **Crews** are `Agent` + `Task` collections that collaborate to deliver results\n- Flows call Crews, get results back, continue\n\n---\n\n### Core Concepts\n| Concept | Key Fields |\n|---|---|\n| `Agent` | role, goal, backstory, tools, LLM, memory, allow_delegation |\n| `Task` | description, expected_output, agent, context, guardrails |\n| `Crew` | agents[], tasks[], process (Sequential/Hierarchical) |\n\n---\n\n### Process Models\n- **Sequential**: Tasks run in order; each output is next task's context\n- **Hierarchical**: Auto-generated manager agent distributes work; hub-and-spoke communication only\n- **Consensual**: Planned but not yet released\n\n---\n\n### Agent Communication\n**Hub-and-spoke only** — no peer-to-peer. All agent coordination goes through the manager. Delegation allows agents to hand off subtasks but only within the hierarchy. This is CrewAI's most significant architectural constraint vs. AutoGen.\n\n---\n\n### Tools System\n- Built-in tools: web search, scraping, file I/O, code execution\n- Custom tools via `BaseTool` subclass or `@tool` decorator\n- **MCP integration**: `mcps=[\"snowflake\", \"stripe\"]` on agents; auto-discovers tools from 1,000+ MCP servers; bidirectional MCP in Enterprise tier\n\n---\n\n### Memory System\nSingle unified `Memory` class backed by **LanceDB** by default. Hierarchical scope paths (`/agent/researcher`, `/project/alpha`). Composite recall scoring blends semantic similarity + recency decay + importance. Two recall depths: **shallow** (vector search, ~200ms) and **deep** (LLM-guided multi-step). Enterprise supports Qdrant/Weaviate/Pinecone.\n\n---\n\n### 2025–2026 Roadmap\nRecent additions: Qdrant Edge backend, native OpenRouter/DeepSeek/Ollama support, **agent skills**, automatic hierarchical memory isolation, RBAC matrix. Strategic direction: enterprise governance, hallucination detection, event bus observability, scaling to thousands of concurrent workflows.\n\n---\n\n### Strengths\nFast to start, role-based model maps naturally to team structures, MIT license, LLM-agnostic, rich MCP ecosystem, strong community.\n\n### Weaknesses\n- Hub-and-spoke only (no P2P agents)\n- Rigid for dynamic/non-task-decomposable workflows\n- Struggles with small open-source models (7B parameter function-calling failures)\n- OSS observability requires external tools (Langfuse, Arize)\n- No built-in plan approval or output refinement step\n\n---\n\n### Acteon-Swarm Positioning\nFrom `swarm.toml`, acteon-swarm has features CrewAI lacks natively:\n| Feature | CrewAI | Acteon-Swarm |\n|---|---|---|\n| Output refiner | ❌ | ✅ (`enable_refiner = true`) |\n| Plan approval gate | ❌ | ✅ (`require_plan_approval`) |\n| Subtask timeout | Not configurable | ✅ (900s) |\n| Namespace isolation | ❌ | ✅ (via tesserai service) |\n| Agent cap | RAM-bound | 8 (configurable) |\n\n---\n\n### No results for \"acteon-swarm\"\nNo public web presence found — it appears to be the **internal project** defined in `swarm.toml`, not a public framework." ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "b70b8183-fc29-4934-a142-feb046e890bc" ;
