	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/structured_data> "null" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "a0468aff-ce34-42cc-aca1-e39a62e19fa8" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "episodic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-28T15:13:46.485874+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Written to `research/frameworks/openai-swarm.md`. Here's a summary of what's covered:\n\n- **Overview** — experimental/educational status, October 2024 release, superseded by OpenAI Agents SDK in March 2025, design philosophy\n- **Architecture** — all four core concepts (agents, routines, handoffs, context variables) with working code examples\n- **Communication model** — direct function-based handoffs, no message bus, linear single-active-agent execution\n- **Tool system** — plain Python functions, automatic JSON schema generation, `str`/`Agent`/`Result` return conventions\n- **Memory** — deliberately absent; context variables as the only in-run shared state\n- **GitHub stats** — 21,200+ stars, MIT, 2,300+ forks, superseded status\n- **Strengths/Weaknesses** — balanced assessment\n- **Comparison table** — acteon-swarm vs OpenAI Swarm across 7 dimensions (metaphor, orchestration, state, parallelism, scope, tooling, use case)\n\nWord count is approximately 950 words, within the 800–1200 target." ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
