	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Written to `research/frameworks/camel.md` (~1,050 words). The file covers all required sections:\n\n- **Overview** — KAUST/NeurIPS 2023 origins, Apache 2.0, pip install\n- **Architecture** — inception prompting mechanics, the three coordinated system prompts, working `RolePlaying` code example\n- **Communication model** — `BaseMessage` turn-based exchange, `Workforce` multi-agent coordination with code\n- **Tool system** — Toolkit pattern, table of 10+ built-in toolkits, MCP/LangChain integration\n- **Memory** — per-agent context window strategies, RAG pipeline with Qdrant/Milvus/pgvector, `VectorRetriever` code example\n- **GitHub & Community** — 16.5k stars, 30k community, 500+ academic citations, OWL extension (19.3k stars)\n- **Strengths/Weaknesses** — balanced 5-point assessments each\n- **Comparison table** — 9-dimension table vs acteon-swarm with clear guidance on when to choose each" ;
